{"title":"2021 Evil Insurgent takes on MX and 27.5″ forms, Super Boosts travel to 168mm","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/08/2021-evil-insurgent-takes-on-mx-and-27-5-forms-super-boosts-travel-to-168mm/","date":1623175254000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>For 2021, Evil have launched not one but two Insurgent mountain bikes to choose from. With mullets popping up on many brand menus this year, it is no surprise to see the Evil Insurgent MX released beside the more recognizable 27.5″ Insurgent. The former is pitted for bike park and freeride, while the latter is the preferred weapon for slaying steep enduro trails. Here’s everything you need to know about the 2021 Evil Insurgent bikes.</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" data-ezsrc=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/559139377?color=a5865e&amp;title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p><p><em>Paul Genovese, Kyle Norbraten and Soren Farenholtz shred the trails on the Sunshine Coast, British Columbia</em></p><figure id=\"attachment_261361\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-261361\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside.jpg\" alt=\"2021 evil insurgent\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb14 src ng ngcb14 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125401/evil-insurgent-2021-outside-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-261361\">The 2021 Evil Insurgent MX and 27.5″ bikes run the same carbon frame</figcaption></figure><p>The 2021 Evil Insurgent gets a massive increase in rear wheel travel from 151mm to 168mm, true for both the 27.5″ and MX option. That’s still delivered by Evil’s easily-recognizable Delta suspension platform, though the swingarm is now wider, stiffer, and can accommodate wider tires with the upgrade to Super Boost. Let’s dive into the numbers.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>Evil Insurgent MX</td><td>Evil Insurgent 27.5″</td></tr><tr><td>Wheel Size</td><td>27.5″ rear, 29″ front</td><td>27.5″ front and rear</td></tr><tr><td>Fork Travel</td><td>170mm</td><td>180mm</td></tr><tr><td>Rear Wheel Travel</td><td>168mm</td><td>168mm</td></tr><tr><td>Head Angle (Low)</td><td>64.2°</td><td>65.3°</td></tr><tr><td>Seat Angle (Low)</td><td>76.9°</td><td>78.2°</td></tr><tr><td>Starting Price</td><td>$5,890 USD</td><td>$5,890 USD</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Insurgent 27.5″</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate.jpg\" alt=\"2021 evil insurgent 27.5\" width=\"1200\" height=\"840\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-297x208.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-800x560.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-120x84.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-768x538.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-696x487.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-1068x748.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-600x420.jpg 600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-100x70.jpg 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb14 src ng ngcb14 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-297x208.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-800x560.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-120x84.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-768x538.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-696x487.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-1068x748.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-600x420.jpg 600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124953/2021-evil-insurgent-275-clean-slate-100x70.jpg 100w\"></a></p><p>This is how the Insurgent began its life on the trails, as a 27.5″ bike that was clearly far more about having fun that it was about winning enduro races. Evil are keeping it in the lineup with 168mm rear wheel travel paired with a 180mm fork. They present it as the best option for bike park shredders and those with freeride ambitions.</p><p>Not only does it see a huge travel upgrade, the geometry is overhauled too. And, as with most single-crown full suspension bikes on the market today, geometry is adjustable via a flip-chip. Altering geometry requires removal of the upper and lower bone link bolts and then removal of three flip-chip bolts, replacing them at 180° relative to their former orientation.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb.jpg\" alt=\"2021 evil insurgent 27.5&quot; 168mm travel enduro mtb\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb14 src ng ngcb14 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08124959/2021-evil-insurgent-275-mtb-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Notably, in comparison with the V1 Insurgent of 2017, the seat tube angle virtually sits bolt upright. It’s moved from a laid back 74.4° straight to 78.2°. This should make the joy of pedaling a 168mm travel bike up hills a lot more joyful.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-4\"></span></p><p>The head angle is slacker, too. In the low position it sits at 65.3°, slackening off to 64.7° in the extra low position. The new Insurgent frames come with a Works Components 1° ZS44/ZS62 Integrated Angle Headset, increasing scope for further geometry adjustments.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb.jpg\" alt=\"2021 evil insurgent 27.5\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb14 src ng ngcb14 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125013/evil-insurgent-2021-275-mtb-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-4\"></span>Changing the orientation of the flip-chip affects the seat tube angle too, dropping it to 77.5°. It also affects the bottom bracket height, reducing it by 8mm, reach and (less so) the effective rear centre length.</p><p>While most brands are increasing reach figures by 5-10mm, Evil have been a little more ambitious in stretching out the Insurgent. For context; the 2017 Insurgent XL frame had a reach of 468mm. Now, in 2021, the <em>medium</em> frame has a longer reach than that, coming in at 473mm. That puts reach for the XL frame at a whopping 512mm in the low geometry position, and 506mm in the extra low position.</p><figure id=\"attachment_261362\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-261362\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike.jpg\" alt=\"2021 evil insurgent freeride bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb14 src ng ngcb14 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125723/2021-evil-insurgent-275-huge-jump-bike-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-261362\">Though the stock bikes come with single crown forks only, Evil do approve use of 180mm+ travel dual-crown forks too</figcaption></figure><p>As you might imagine, the 2021 Evil Insurgent is significantly longer than the original, thanks to that slacker head angle and longer reach, though they’ve kept chainstays short at 430mm. The wheelbase of a medium frame is now 1233mm, an increase of 55mm. While a longer bike will be a good thing for most, the changes may well leave shorter riders behind. The original small Insurgent serviced riders down to 5′ 3″, but the new reach of 449mm will surely be a stretch for them. That said, the MX version may offer an alternative.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08114328/2021-evil-insurgent-275-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08114328/2021-evil-insurgent-275-geometry-chart.jpg\" alt=\"2021 evil insurgent\" width=\"1200\" height=\"926\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08114328/2021-evil-insurgent-275-geometry-chart.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08114328/2021-evil-insurgent-275-geometry-chart-297x229.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08114328/2021-evil-insurgent-275-geometry-chart-800x617.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08114328/2021-evil-insurgent-275-geometry-chart-120x93.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08114328/2021-evil-insurgent-275-geometry-chart-768x593.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08114328/2021-evil-insurgent-275-geometry-