erumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125007/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-clean-slate.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125007/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-clean-slate-297x208.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125007/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-clean-slate-800x560.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125007/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-clean-slate-120x84.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125007/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-clean-slate-768x538.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125007/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-clean-slate-696x487.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125007/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-clean-slate-1068x748.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125007/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-clean-slate-600x420.jpg 600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125007/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-clean-slate-100x70.jpg 100w\"></a></p><p>The 2021 Insurgent MX runs a 170mm fork and 29″ front wheel, while the 27.5″ rear wheel runs 168mm travel. Though it is the exact same frame as the 27.5″ counterpart, the taller front end kicks the head angle back to 64.2° in the low geometry position and 63.5° in the extra low position.&nbsp;<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-large-leaderboard-2\"></span></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125920/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-manual.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125920/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-manual.jpg\