3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125920/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-manual-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125920/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-manual-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125920/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-manual-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125920/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-manual-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08125920/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-manual-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The seat angle sees a similar change, sitting at 76.9° in the low position. Of course, the bottom bracket sits higher, too, at 358mm. Reach figures span a 443mm to 500mm across the S-XL frame size range, making this the better option for riders at the shorter end of the spectrum.</p><h3><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart.jpg\" alt=\"2021 evil insurgent mx geometry\" width=\"1200\" height=\"935\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-297x231.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-800x623.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-120x94.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-768x598.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-696x542.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-1068x832.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-539x420.jpg 539w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb14 src ng ngcb14 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-297x231.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-800x623.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-120x94.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-768x598.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-696x542.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-1068x832.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08120500/2021-evil-insurgent-mx-geometry-chart-539x420.jpg 539w\"></a>Insurgent Frame Details</h3><p>The Evil Insurgent gets Super Boost spacing for 2021, now permitting clearance for a 2.6″ wide tire on the 27.5″ rear wheel. This change has allowed Evil to widen the main pivot hardware, increasing stiffness and strength.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage.jpg\" alt=\"2021 evil insurgent delta suspension trunnion mount shock\" width=\"1200\" height=\"942\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-297x233.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-800x628.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-120x94.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-768x603.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-696x546.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-1068x838.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-535x420.jpg 535w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb14 src ng ngcb14 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-297x233.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-800x628.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-120x94.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-768x603.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-696x546.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-1068x838.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/08130148/2021-evil-insurgent-delta-suspension-linkage-535x420.jpg 535w\"></a></p><p>The Insurgent’s Delta System runs a Trunnion mount shock, meaning dual row angular contact bearings (instead of bushings) actuate the shock for what is said to be buttery smooth suspension.</p><p>The carbon frame makes use of a threaded bottom bracket. Above the chainring sits an integrated chain guide, adjustable for 30T-36T chain rings. It features built-in silencing rubber to keep it quiet on the trail. Cable routing is internal and fully guided throughout. Lastly, the Insurgent frame is finished off with molded rubber downtube and driveside swingarm protectors.</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>The 2021 Evil Insurgent is available frame only from $3,190 USD with a RockShox Super Deluxe Ultimate Coil shock, though you can spend more by upgrading to a FOX X2 or Push ELEVENSIX.&nbsp;</p><p>Complete build pricing starts from $5,890, featuring a RockShox Super Deluxe Ultimate Coil shock, ZEB Ultimate fork, SRAM G2 RS brakes and GX Eagle 12 speed group.</p><p>For full details on pricing and availability, head to the Evil Bikes website.</p><p><a href=\"https://eu.evil-bikes.com/a/bikes/insurgent\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Evil-Bikes.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"59cc39f961ccc103a5c08bcf19acaeb9ea01ebbb39ae1c066496adcb46b0034e","category":"Cycling"}